          "id": "f8eb38b53140470c3b8383759c8e05c97656c730",
          "message": "docs(cli): generate the CLI reference from Click commands (#2033)\n\n## Summary\n\nStarted as a manual refresh of the CLI reference pages; review surfaced\nthat hand-written pages drift from the code (stale options, undocumented\ncommands), so the PR now replaces them with **build-time generation from\nthe Click command tree** — the same treatment quartodoc gives the Python\nAPI reference. Command docstrings become the single source of truth for\nboth `--help` and the docs site.\n\n## What changed\n\n### Generator (`docs/generate_cli_reference.py`)\n- Walks `xorq.cli` + `xorq.catalog.cli`, emits one page per command plus\na grouped `index.qmd` (40 pages, including previously undocumented `uv\nrun-cached` / `uv run-unbound`)\n- Parses docstring `\\b Arguments:` / `\\b Examples:` literal blocks into\npage sections; other paragraphs pass through as markdown\n- Curated config in the script: nav grouping/order, see-also\ncross-links, redirect aliases (`ls`/`rm`); a command missing from the\nnav config is a **hard error**, as is an unhandled nested command group\n\n### Docstrings as the single source (`cli.py`, `catalog/cli.py`,\n`cli_options.py`)\n- All 39 command docstrings enriched with prose, arguments, and examples\nharvested from the old hand-written pages — `xorq <cmd> --help` now\nshows the full reference content\n- `show_default` added across the board (audited programmatically: every\noption with a meaningful default now shows it in `--help`)\n- Docstring prose follows the docs style rules (Vale lints the generated\npages)\n\n### Pipeline\n- `docs/api_reference/cli/` is gitignored and generated by `just\ndocs-apigen`; the 39 committed pages and the unconsumed\n`cli/_sidebar.yml` are removed\n- Nav: explicit `_quarto.yml` entries replaced by `auto:` globs sorted\nby generated `order` frontmatter\n- `ci-docs-lint` generates before Vale (docstring prose is style-checked\nin CI); `lint.sh` gains check 0 (generate) and excludes the generated\ntree from the textual orphan scan (the generator enforces nav coverage\nitself)\n\n### Content note\nThe tutorial-style walkthroughs the old\n`build`/`run`/`serve-flight-udxf` pages carried are already covered by\nthe quickstart (serve + client flow) and the your-first-build tutorial;\nthe remaining unique snippets moved into the docstrings.\n\n## Verification\n- `just docs-lint` green end to end: CLI generation, Vale, quartodoc,\n`quarto render`, lychee (0 broken of ~6800 links), pymarkdown,\nfrontmatter, orphans\n- Sidebar order verified in the rendered site; help/option tests pass;\npages regenerate byte-stable\n\nPart of the Diataxis docs effort — #2023 (Phase 0a: #2024).\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
